    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="95"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d95">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/1408</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1782</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-13">April 13,
                            1935</date>.<lb/>[Received April 24.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Embassy’s despatch No. 1253 of
                    October 2, 1934,<note n="10" xml:id="d95fn10">Not printed.</note> and to the
                    recent sale of the Chinese Eastern Railway, I have <pb facs="0225" n="113"
                        xml:id="pg_113"/> the honor to report, as a matter of record, that the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs, in reply to a written question by Deputy Susset,
                    published a statement on page 4153 of the <hi rend="italic">Journal
                        Officiel</hi> of April 12, 1935, confirming that the French Government had
                    intervened for the purpose of protecting French private interests in the Chinese
                    Eastern Railway.</p>
                <p>The Minister emphasised that “very explicit reserves had once more been conveyed
                    to the Soviet and Japanese Governments immediately following the definitive
                    conclusion of the arrangement relating to this enterprise”.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Ambassador:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. Merle Cochran</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">First Secretary of Embassy</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
